---
import PresentationLayout from '~/layouts/PresentationLayout.astro';

const metadata = {
  title: 'Agentic Coding: Foundation and Mindset',
  description: 'Understanding the foundation and mindset needed to work effectively with agentic coding tools.',
  ignoreTitleTemplate: false,
};
---

<PresentationLayout metadata={metadata}>
  <!-- Slide 1: Title -->
  <section data-state="title" class="title-slide">
    <h1>Agentic Coding</h1>
    <h2>Foundation and Mindset</h2>
  </section>

  <!-- Slide 2: About Me -->
  <section>
    <h2>About Me</h2>
    <div
      style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.25rem; margin-top: 2rem; max-width: 80%; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"
    >
      <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem;">
        <span style="font-size: 1.5rem; min-width: 2rem; text-align: center;">🛠️</span>
        <p style="margin: 0;">15 years of software engineering experience</p>
      </div>
      <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem;">
        <span style="font-size: 1.5rem; min-width: 2rem; text-align: center;">❤️</span>
        <p style="margin: 0;">I genuinely enjoy coding and building software</p>
      </div>
      <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem;">
        <span style="font-size: 1.5rem; min-width: 2rem; text-align: center;">🏗️</span>
        <p style="margin: 0;">Currently building <strong>Agewise</strong> as CTO</p>
      </div>
      <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem;">
        <span style="font-size: 1.5rem; min-width: 2rem; text-align: center;">🤖</span>
        <p style="margin: 0;">Me and my team delegate <strong>99% of coding</strong> to AI agents</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Slide 3: Agenda -->
  <section>
    <h2>Agenda</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Possibilities — What AI Can Do Today</li>
      <li>AI Adoption - Why It Fails</li>
      <li>Mindset For Successful Adoption</li>
      <li>Foundations</li>
      <li>Where to Start</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 1: Possibilities -->

  <!-- Slide 4: What Can Be Delegated to AI -->
  <section>
    <h2>What Can Be Delegated to AI</h2>
    <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 1.25rem; margin-top: 1.5rem;">
      <div class="content-box">
        <span class="content-box-icon">⚡</span>
        <div class="content-box-content">
          <h3>Code Generation</h3>
          <p style="color: #a0aec0;">Features, handlers, components, APIs — from specification to working code</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="content-box">
        <span class="content-box-icon">🧪</span>
        <div class="content-box-content">
          <h3>Test Generation</h3>
          <p style="color: #a0aec0;">Unit, integration, and E2E tests following your existing patterns</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="content-box">
        <span class="content-box-icon">👁️</span>
        <div class="content-box-content">
          <h3>Code Reviews</h3>
          <p style="color: #a0aec0;">PRs reviewed against acceptance criteria, performance, and your standards</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="content-box">
        <span class="content-box-icon">🔄</span>
        <div class="content-box-content">
          <h3>Mass Refactorings</h3>
          <p style="color: #a0aec0;">Rename, restructure, migrate patterns across the entire codebase</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="content-box" style="grid-column: 1 / -1; max-width: 50%; margin: 0 auto;">
        <span class="content-box-icon">🐛</span>
        <div class="content-box-content">
          <h3>Debugging & Bug Fixes</h3>
          <p style="color: #a0aec0;">From stack trace to pull request</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Slide 5: Thinking is the New Bottleneck -->
  <section>
    <h2>Thinking is the New Bottleneck</h2>
    <div style="text-align: center; margin-top: 3rem;">
      <p style="font-size: 1.3rem; color: #e2e8f0; line-height: 1.8;">
        I delegate 99% of coding to AI agents.<br />
        The quality of my code has never been higher.
      </p>
      <p style="font-size: 1.3rem; color: #e2e8f0; line-height: 1.8; margin-top: 2rem;">
        I spend more time <strong>thinking</strong> than writing code.<br />
        My bottleneck isn't coding anymore —<br />
        it's <strong>deciding what to build and how</strong>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 2: Why It Fails -->

  <!-- Slide 9: Common Failure Patterns -->
  <section>
    <h2>Common Failure Patterns</h2>
    <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 2rem;">
      <div class="content-box red">
        <span class="content-box-icon">🌪️</span>
        <div class="content-box-content">
          <h3>Dropping AI randomly across the project</h3>
          <p style="color: #a0aec0;">
            It works in some places, fails in others. Each layer needs focused attention before AI can deliver
            consistently.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="content-box red">
        <span class="content-box-icon">🤖</span>
        <div class="content-box-content">
          <h3>Giving up architectural control</h3>
          <p style="color: #a0aec0;">
            Your architecture is your boundary. When AI makes structural decisions you didn't ask for, you lose control
            of your system.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="content-box red">
        <span class="content-box-icon">🏗️</span>
        <div class="content-box-content">
          <h3>Letting AI loose</h3>
          <p style="color: #a0aec0;">
            Not reviewing the plan, not checking the approach. Leads to uncontrolled decisions baked into your codebase.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="content-box red">
        <span class="content-box-icon">🎯</span>
        <div class="content-box-content">
          <h3>Weak prompts, expecting magic</h3>
          <p style="color: #a0aec0;">Vague input, vague output. Then the conclusion is "AI isn't ready yet."</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Slide 10: AI on a Broken Foundation -->
  <section>
    <h2 style="text-align: center; color: #0ea5c1; margin-bottom: 2rem;">AI on a Broken Foundation</h2>
    <p style="font-size: 1.6rem; font-weight: 600; text-align: center; color: #e2e8f0; margin-bottom: 3rem;">
      AI doesn't fix broken processes. It amplifies them.
    </p>
    <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 2rem;">
      <div class="content-box red">
        <span class="content-box-icon">🎲</span>
        <div class="content-box-content">
          <h3>Inconsistent Output</h3>
          <p style="color: #a0aec0;">
            AI generates different solutions for the same problem. No patterns, no standards.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="content-box red">
        <span class="content-box-icon">👀</span>
        <div class="content-box-content">
          <h3>Quality Collapse</h3>
          <p style="color: #a0aec0;">Bad patterns get copy-pasted by AI. Technical debt compounds daily.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="content-box red">
        <span class="content-box-icon">🧪</span>
        <div class="content-box-content">
          <h3>Technical Debt Spiral</h3>
          <p style="color: #a0aec0;">AI writes implementation. Humans skip tests. Maintenance costs explode.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="content-box red">
        <span class="content-box-icon">🤷</span>
        <div class="content-box-content">
          <h3>Blame Deflection</h3>
          <p style="color: #a0aec0;">
            "AI isn't ready yet" / "Our domain is too complex" / "The AI doesn't understand our codebase"
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Slide 11: The DORA Reality -->
  <section>
    <div style="text-align: center;">
      <blockquote
        style="font-size: 1.8rem; font-weight: 600; color: #0ea5c1; margin: 3rem auto; padding: 0; line-height: 1.4; max-width: 90%;"
      >
        "AI magnifies the strengths of high-performing organizations and the dysfunctions of struggling ones."
      </blockquote>
      <p style="font-size: 1.2rem; color: #a0aec0; margin-bottom: 3rem;">— DORA Report 2025</p>
      <p style="font-size: 1.1rem; color: #e2e8f0; margin-top: 2rem;">
        The gap between elite and struggling teams isn't staying the same.<br />
        <strong style="color: #0ea5c1;">AI is actively widening it.</strong>
      </p>
      <p style="font-size: 1.2rem; color: #e2e8f0; margin-top: 2.5rem; line-height: 1.6;">
        AI-assisted coding is built on <strong>traditional software engineering</strong>.<br />
        The stronger your habits and fundamentals, the better your results.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 3: Mindset -->

  <!-- Slide 12: Hype vs Reality -->
  <section>
    <h2>The Hype vs Reality</h2>
    <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 2rem; align-items: start;">
      <div>
        <h3>The Hype</h3>
        <ul style="list-style: none;">
          <li>❌ AI builds features autonomously</li>
          <li>❌ AI replaces developers</li>
          <li>❌ 10x productivity overnight</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3>Reality</h3>
        <ul style="list-style: none;">
          <li>✅ AI helps <strong>YOU</strong> building features</li>
          <li>✅ AI empowers software engineers</li>
          <li>✅ &gt;1x productivity with proper setup</li>
          <li>⚠️ Hurts productivity if misused</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Slide 13: Vibe Coding vs. AI-Assisted -->
  <section>
    <h2>Vibe Coding vs. AI-Assisted Coding</h2>
    <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin-top: 2rem; font-size: 0.85rem;">
      <thead>
        <tr style="border-bottom: 2px solid #0ea5c1;">
          <th style="text-align: left; padding: 1rem; background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.1);">Aspect</th>
          <th style="text-align: left; padding: 1rem; background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.1);">Vibe Coding</th>
          <th style="text-align: left; padding: 1rem; background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.1);">AI-Assisted Coding</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid #374151;">
          <td style="padding: 0.75rem; font-weight: 600;">Prompting &<br />Context</td>
          <td style="padding: 0.75rem; color: #a0aec0;">Feature description</td>
          <td style="padding: 0.75rem; color: #a0aec0;">Feature description + technical details</td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid #374151;">
          <td style="padding: 0.75rem; font-weight: 600;">Guidelines</td>
          <td style="padding: 0.75rem; color: #a0aec0;">Don't exist or weak</td>
          <td style="padding: 0.75rem; color: #a0aec0;">Well-defined constraints</td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid #374151;">
          <td style="padding: 0.75rem; font-weight: 600;">Code Quality</td>
          <td style="padding: 0.75rem; color: #a0aec0;">Unpredictable</td>
          <td style="padding: 0.75rem; color: #a0aec0;">Consistent with codebase</td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid #374151;">
          <td style="padding: 0.75rem; font-weight: 600;">Codebase<br />Scalability</td>
          <td style="padding: 0.75rem; color: #a0aec0;">😐</td>
          <td style="padding: 0.75rem; color: #a0aec0;">Grows by following existing patterns</td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid #374151;">
          <td style="padding: 0.75rem; font-weight: 600;">Productivity</td>
          <td style="padding: 0.75rem; color: #a0aec0;">High at first, collapses quickly</td>
          <td style="padding: 0.75rem; color: #a0aec0;">Consistently high</td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid #374151;">
          <td style="padding: 0.75rem; font-weight: 600;">Team Impact</td>
          <td style="padding: 0.75rem; color: #a0aec0;">There can't be a team 😐</td>
          <td style="padding: 0.75rem; color: #a0aec0;">Less manual work, focus on complex problems</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td style="padding: 0.75rem; font-weight: 600;">Emotions</td>
          <td style="padding: 0.75rem; color: #a0aec0;">Hope</td>
          <td style="padding: 0.75rem; color: #a0aec0;">Joy</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <!-- Slide 14: Junior Developer Mental Model -->
  <section>
    <h2>The "Junior Developer" Mental Model</h2>
    <p>Think of AI as a talented junior developer on your team.</p>
    <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1rem; margin-top: 1.5rem;">
      <div class="content-box">
        <span class="content-box-icon">📋</span>
        <div class="content-box-content">
          <h3>Good examples to follow</h3>
          <p style="color: #a0aec0;">Find similar implementation and replicate</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="content-box">
        <span class="content-box-icon">🏗️</span>
        <div class="content-box-content">
          <h3>Clear boundaries</h3>
          <p style="color: #a0aec0;">
            Well-organized codebase speaks for itself — conventions show the way, not documentation
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="content-box">
        <span class="content-box-icon">🔄</span>
        <div class="content-box-content">
          <h3>Feedback</h3>
          <p style="color: #a0aec0;">What is wrong, what was broken — tests, linters, code review</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="content-box">
        <span class="content-box-icon">🎯</span>
        <div class="content-box-content">
          <h3>Objective</h3>
          <p style="color: #a0aec0;">What to implement, new behaviors, how to implement it</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div
      style="border: 2px solid #0ea5c1; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem; background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.15); margin-top: 1.5rem;"
    >
      <p style="margin: 0; text-align: center;">
        <strong>You are the brain. AI is your hands.</strong>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 4: Foundations -->

  <!-- Bridge: What Does AI Need From You? -->
  <section>
    <h2>So What Does AI Need From You?</h2>
    <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.25rem; margin-top: 2rem;">
      <div
        style="border: 3px solid #4ade80; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem; background: rgba(74, 222, 128, 0.1);"
      >
        <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-size: 1.3rem;">Clean, Consistent Codebase</h3>
        <p style="color: #a0aec0; margin: 0; font-size: 1rem;">
          Good examples + clear boundaries — AI replicates what it sees
        </p>
      </div>

      <div
        style="border: 3px solid #0ea5c1; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem; background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.1);"
      >
        <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-size: 1.3rem;">Strong Prompts With Context</h3>
        <p style="color: #a0aec0; margin: 0; font-size: 1rem;">Clear objective — what to implement, how, and why</p>
      </div>

      <div
        style="border: 3px solid #f0c36d; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem; background: rgba(240, 195, 109, 0.1);"
      >
        <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-size: 1.3rem;">Feedback Loop</h3>
        <p style="color: #a0aec0; margin: 0; font-size: 1rem;">
          Tests, linters, code review — what is wrong, what was broken
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Pillar 1: Codebase = Training Data -->
  <section>
    <h2>Your Codebase = Training Data</h2>
    <p style="color: #a0aec0; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">AI is pattern-matching, not magic</p>
    <div style="text-align: center;">
      <p style="font-size: 2.5rem; font-weight: 700; color: #0ea5c1; margin: 1.5rem 0;">Garbage In ⇒ Garbage Out</p>
      <p style="font-size: 1.1rem; color: #a0aec0;">Your codebase quality directly determines AI output quality.</p>
      <div
        style="border: 2px solid #ef4444; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem; background: rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.1); margin-top: 2rem;"
      >
        <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 1.1rem;">
          One bad pattern in your codebase becomes <strong>ten bad patterns</strong> by the end of the day.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Pillar 2: Weak Prompts → Weak Results -->
  <section>
    <h2>Weak Prompts → Weak Results</h2>
    <div style="text-align: center; margin-top: 2rem;">
      <p style="font-size: 1.3rem; color: #e2e8f0; line-height: 1.8;">
        Vague instructions produce vague code.<br />
        Without constraints, architecture context, and clear scope,<br />
        <strong>AI guesses wrong</strong>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Pillar 3: No Feedback → No Safety Net -->
  <section>
    <h2>No Feedback → No Safety Net</h2>
    <div style="text-align: center; margin-top: 2rem;">
      <p style="font-size: 1.2rem; color: #e2e8f0; line-height: 1.8;">
        More code → no automated checks → bugs compound → endless manual review
      </p>
      <div
        style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr auto 1fr auto 1fr auto 1fr; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem; margin: 2.5rem auto; max-width: 95%;"
      >
        <span
          style="background: rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.2); border: 1px solid #ef4444; padding: 0.75rem 0.75rem; border-radius: 8px; text-align: center; font-size: 0.9rem;"
          >AI writes code</span
        >
        <span style="color: #ef4444; font-size: 1.5rem; text-align: center;">→</span>
        <span
          style="background: rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.2); border: 1px solid #ef4444; padding: 0.75rem 0.75rem; border-radius: 8px; text-align: center; font-size: 0.9rem;"
          >No automated checks</span
        >
        <span style="color: #ef4444; font-size: 1.5rem; text-align: center;">→</span>
        <span
          style="background: rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.2); border: 1px solid #ef4444; padding: 0.75rem 0.75rem; border-radius: 8px; text-align: center; font-size: 0.9rem;"
          >Bugs compound</span
        >
        <span style="color: #ef4444; font-size: 1.5rem; text-align: center;">→</span>
        <span
          style="background: rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.2); border: 1px solid #ef4444; padding: 0.75rem 0.75rem; border-radius: 8px; text-align: center; font-size: 0.9rem;"
          >Endless manual review</span
        >
      </div>
      <div
        style="border: 2px solid #4ade80; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem; background: rgba(74, 222, 128, 0.1); margin-top: 1.5rem;"
      >
        <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 1.1rem;">
          <strong>Tests, linters, and code review</strong> let AI verify its own work. Without them, you're just producing
          bugs faster.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Slide 21: The 3-Layer Approach -->
  <section>
    <h3 style="margin-bottom: 1rem;">The 3-Layer Approach</h3>
    <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1rem;">
      <div
        style="border: 3px solid #4ade80; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1rem 1.25rem; background: rgba(74, 222, 128, 0.1); position: relative;"
      >
        <span
          style="position: absolute; top: 0.75rem; right: 1rem; background: white; color: black; padding: 0.35rem 0.75rem; border-radius: 6px; font-weight: 700; font-size: 0.75rem;"
          >Most Important</span
        >
        <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0.35rem; font-size: 1.3rem;">Layer 1: Codebase</h3>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 0.35rem; font-size: 1rem;"><strong>Consistency and good examples</strong></p>
        <p style="font-style: italic; color: #a0aec0; font-size: 0.9rem;">
          Example: Existing handlers show the pattern
        </p>
      </div>

      <div
        style="border: 3px solid #0ea5c1; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1rem 1.25rem; background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.1); position: relative;"
      >
        <span
          style="position: absolute; top: 0.75rem; right: 1rem; background: white; color: black; padding: 0.35rem 0.75rem; border-radius: 6px; font-weight: 700; font-size: 0.75rem;"
          >Supplements</span
        >
        <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0.35rem; font-size: 1.3rem;">Layer 2: Guidelines</h3>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 0.35rem; font-size: 1rem;"><strong>Navigates, restricts, clarifies</strong></p>
        <p style="font-style: italic; color: #a0aec0; font-size: 0.9rem;">
          Example: Use error middleware, validate with Zod
        </p>
      </div>

      <div
        style="border: 3px solid #f0c36d; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1rem 1.25rem; background: rgba(240, 195, 109, 0.1); position: relative;"
      >
        <span
          style="position: absolute; top: 0.75rem; right: 1rem; background: white; color: black; padding: 0.35rem 0.75rem; border-radius: 6px; font-weight: 700; font-size: 0.75rem;"
          >Reference Implementation</span
        >
        <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0.35rem; font-size: 1.3rem;">Layer 3: References</h3>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 0.35rem; font-size: 1rem;"><strong>Point AI to similar existing code</strong></p>
        <p style="font-style: italic; color: #a0aec0; font-size: 0.9rem;">
          Example: "Similar implementation we have in /handlers/auth/login.ts"
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 5: Where to Start -->

  <!-- Slide 22: Where to Start -->
  <section>
    <h2>Where to Start</h2>
    <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1rem; margin-top: 1.5rem;">
      <div class="content-box">
        <span class="content-box-icon">🌱</span>
        <div class="content-box-content">
          <h3>Start Small</h3>
          <p style="color: #a0aec0;">
            Unit tests, HTTP handlers, API calls. My recommendation — start with automated tests, you'll need them.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="content-box">
        <span class="content-box-icon">📋</span>
        <div class="content-box-content">
          <h3>Make Strong Examples First</h3>
          <p style="color: #a0aec0;">Establish architecture and patterns, then let AI replicate. Don't let AI loose.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="content-box">
        <span class="content-box-icon">🔄</span>
        <div class="content-box-content">
          <h3>Iterate and Improve</h3>
          <p style="color: #a0aec0;">Refine guidelines based on actual output until it's near-perfect.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="content-box">
        <span class="content-box-icon">📈</span>
        <div class="content-box-content">
          <h3>Expand</h3>
